   @eolivelli @kezhuw @anmolnar could you please review https://github.com/apache/zookeeper/pull/2269? This change implements our paranoid security recommendation: each ZooKeeper quorum member must present a distinct mTLS certificate, validated against its CNAME. The patch adds the ability to configure authentication for both quorum servers and learners—very similar to the work tracked in https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-2123

